You need to explicitly tell angular to get full response not just body.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
By default angular httpClient return only body. In order to get full response you need to add&lt;br/&gt; `observe: &#39;response&#39;` in httpOptions something like this


    var headers = new Headers();
        headers.append(&#39;Content-Type&#39;, &#39;application/json&#39;);
        let httpOptions = new RequestOptions({ headers: headers, withCredentials: true, observe: &#39;response&#39; });
    
     return this.http.post(url, data, httpOptions)
       .subscribe(res =&gt; {
                 console.log(&#39;response&#39;, res);
               });
     });

for more details see [angular docs - reading full response][1]

  [1]: https://angular.io/guide/http#reading-the-full-response

